You must EDIT the HTTPServer constructor to accept dependency injection.

## Task F6: HTTPServer constructor injection

**File**: `D:\code\temp\SpecForge\packages\daemon-core\src\http\HTTPServer.ts`

### Step 1: Add the HTTPServerDeps interface

After the existing imports (around line 26), add:

```ts
import { StateManager } from '../state/StateManager';
import { WAL } from '../wal/WAL';

export interface HTTPServerDeps {
  config: DaemonConfig;
  eventBus: EventBus;
  stateManager: StateManager;
  wal: WAL;
  permissionEngine?: any;  // @specforge/permission-engine - optional until F13
  workflowEngine?: any;    // @specforge/workflow-runtime - optional until F14
  eventLogger?: any;       // @specforge/observability - optional until F15
  sessionRegistry?: any;   // optional
}
```

### Step 2: Modify the constructor

The current constructor (around line 78) is:
```ts
constructor(config: DaemonConfig, eventBus?: EventBus) {
  this.config = config;
  this.eventBus = eventBus || null;
  this.cas = new ContentAddressableStorage();
  this.registerDefaultRoutes();
}
```

Change it to accept both the old pattern and new deps pattern:
```ts
private deps: Partial<HTTPServerDeps>;

constructor(configOrDeps: DaemonConfig | HTTPServerDeps, eventBus?: EventBus) {
  if ('config' in configOrDeps && typeof configOrDeps.config === 'object') {
    // New deps-based constructor
    this.deps = configOrDeps;
    this.config = configOrDeps.config;
    this.eventBus = configOrDeps.eventBus || null;
  } else {
    // Legacy constructor for backward compat
    this.deps = {};
    this.config = configOrDeps as DaemonConfig;
    this.eventBus = eventBus || null;
  }
  this.cas = new ContentAddressableStorage();
  this.registerDefaultRoutes();
}
```

Also add a getter for deps:
```ts
getDependencies(): Partial<HTTPServerDeps> {
  return this.deps;
}
```

### Step 3: Update Daemon.ts to use new constructor

Read `D:\code\temp\SpecForge\packages\daemon-core\src\daemon\Daemon.ts` and find where HTTPServer is instantiated. Change it to pass the deps object:

```ts
this.httpServer = new HTTPServer({
  config: this.config,
  eventBus: this.eventBus,
  stateManager: this.stateManager,
  wal: this.wal,
  permissionEngine: this.permissionEngine,
  workflowEngine: this.workflowEngine,
  eventLogger: this.eventLogger,
  sessionRegistry: this.sessionRegistry,
});
```

### Important:
- Keep backward compatibility (the old constructor pattern should still work)
- Read both files before editing
- Don't break existing tests

Return: files modified and confirmation.
